# Trivy ignore list — every entry must include a justification + review date.
# https://trivy.dev/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DS-0002: "Last USER command in Dockerfile should not be 'root'"
#
# Justification:
#   The container intentionally boots as root so docker/entrypoint.sh can
#     1. apply ${PUID}/${PGID} to the in-container `app` user (LinuxServer.io
#        pattern, required for bind-mount writes on Unraid/Synology/etc),
#     2. chown the /app/data volume to that UID/GID,
#     3. drop privileges to `app` via `gosu app "$@"` before exec'ing node.
#   Static analysis cannot follow the runtime gosu drop, so Trivy flags the
#   final USER directive even though the actual node process never runs as
#   root. Equivalent finding is suppressed in linuxserver/* images.
#
# Reviewed: 2026-04-25 (PR #11)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
AVD-DS-0002
DS-0002
